node.text: It's basically like a 12 minute risotto without the need to stir it. The easiest way to get even vegetable resistant kids to WANT to eat them because each bite has confetti like pieces of carrot and broccoli with tons of of flavors in every bite. What other vegetable would you want to add in? 🌶🫑 Recipe link in bio! https://weelicious.com/carrot-broccoli-cheese-orzo/

node.text: What kind of milk do you drink? I started making this homemade milk in different flavors (hello strawberry, chocolate and even green tea 🍵🍓🍫) and its been a game changer. node.text: Now that half of our family is vegetarian, I'm constantly trying to work on flexible recipes to fit everyone's food choices. node.text:
TOSTADA SALAD! The least salad-y salads of all the salads with fresh guacamole, salsa and more! 🥗 CRUNCH-y and fresh, what would you put on yours? Make it fun for your little ones and let them smash the tostada shells and let them break apart over everything. Major win! 💃 👉🏻recipe link in bio👈🏻 ⁣
⁣

BANANA BITES! 🍌🥞 Volume 🆙 Want to shake up pancakes in a way that’s kinda LIFE CHANGING? Just dip banana slices in Weelicious pancake batter (or any batter you love) and sauté them to create these addictive bites. It’s golden pancake surrounding a soft, caramelly banana center. Heaven in every bite! I add a little decadence by dipping them first in chocolate. What would you dip them in? 🍫🥜🍯🍁 Recipe link on Weelicious 💛⁣
⁣
https://weelicious.com/banana-bites/

HOMEMADE FRUIT LEATHER 🍑 I hate wasting food. So, whenever I have overripe or overly bruised fruit I turn it into fruit leather. You can use a single fruit or mix a few different kinds to make a treat that’s both healthy and fun to eat. You can use stone fruit, strawberries, persimmon, mango and more. And if you don’t have a dehydrator, you can use your oven. What fruit would you use? 🍓🫐🥝🥭🍍 Recipe link on Weelicious.com ⬇️⁣
⁣
https://weelicious.com/peach-fruit-leather/
